# 🅿️ Parking Spot Finder — System Architecture

---

## 📌 Project Overview

A web and mobile application that helps users find, reserve, and navigate to available parking spots in real time using GPS, Google Maps, and crowd-sourced data.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Layers

### 1. 🖥️ Client Layer (Frontend)
| Component | Technology |
|-----------|------------|
| Web App | HTML, CSS, JavaScript |
| Mobile App | Android Studio (Java) |
| Map View | Google Maps SDK |
| GPS Module | Browser Geolocation API |

---

### 2. 🔌 API Gateway
| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| Auth Filter | JWT token verification |
| Rate Limiter | Request throttling |
| Router | URL routing & request dispatch |
| Request Logger | Audit trail for all requests |

---

### 3. ⚙️ Backend Services

| Service | Responsibilities |
|---------|-----------------|
| User Service | Register, Login, JWT Auth |
| Parking Service | CRUD, Search, Status Update |
| Location Service | Geo queries, Distance calculation |
| Notification Service | Push alerts, WebSocket |
| Reservation Service | Booking, Timeslot management |
| Payment Service | Fee calculation, Billing |

**Tech Stack:** Java Spring Boot / Node.js

---

### 4. 🗄️ Data Layer (Database)

**Database:** MySQL

#### Tables

**users**
```
id            INT PRIMARY KEY
name          VARCHAR
email         VARCHAR UNIQUE
password_hash VARCHAR
phone         VARCHAR
created_at    TIMESTAMP
```

**parking_spots**
```
id            INT PRIMARY KEY
name          VARCHAR
latitude      DECIMAL
longitude     DECIMAL
status        ENUM('available', 'occupied')
fee_per_hour  DECIMAL
updated_at    TIMESTAMP
```

**reservations**
```
id          INT PRIMARY KEY
user_id     INT FOREIGN KEY → users.id
spot_id     INT FOREIGN KEY → parking_spots.id
start_time  DATETIME
end_time    DATETIME
total_fee   DECIMAL
qr_code     TEXT
```

**availability_logs**
```
id          INT PRIMARY KEY
spot_id     INT FOREIGN KEY → parking_spots.id
marked_by   INT FOREIGN KEY → users.id
old_status  ENUM
new_status  ENUM
changed_at  TIMESTAMP
```

---

### 5. 🌍 External Services

| Service | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| Google Maps API | Maps, Directions, Places |
| Firebase FCM | Push Notifications |
| Stripe / Razorpay | Payment Gateway |
| QR Code Service | Entry / Exit Scanning |

---

## 🔄 Request Data Flow

```
User Opens App
      │
      ▼
GPS fetches current location → Map renders nearby area
      │
      ▼
Auth Check (JWT token validated at API Gateway)
      │
      ▼
Parking Service receives lat/lng → Geo query on DB
      │
      ▼
Available spots returned → Rendered as map markers
      │
      ▼
User selects spot → Reserve / Mark as occupied
      │
      ▼
DB updated → Real-time WebSocket push to other users
      │
      ▼
Google Maps directions + QR code generated for entry
```

---

## 🌐 REST API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | Register new user |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Login & get JWT |
| GET | `/api/parking/nearby?lat&lng&r` | Find nearby spots |
| GET | `/api/parking/{id}` | Get spot details |
| PUT | `/api/parking/{id}/status` | Update spot status |
| POST | `/api/reservations` | Create reservation |
| GET | `/api/reservations/my` | Get user reservations |
| DELETE | `/api/reservations/{id}` | Cancel reservation |
| GET | `/api/directions?from&to` | Get directions |
| POST | `/api/notifications/subscribe` | Subscribe to alerts |

